  <h2>The problem we exist to solve</h2>
  <p>China makes what the world buys. Yet the moment a Western buyer hears your name — at a trade show, through a referral, in an Alibaba message — their next move isn't to reply. It's to look you up on LinkedIn. If they find nothing, they quietly move on, and you never even know they looked.</p>
  <p>World-class factories, agencies, forwarders, and software companies lose deals every day not on quality or price, but on <strong>presence</strong> — because the place where trust is now built is the one place they're invisible.</p>

  <h2>What we do</h2>
  <p>We build and run a done-for-you LinkedIn engine: profile and company-page optimization, monthly content, targeted outreach, and a real pipeline dashboard — so Western buyers find you, remember you, and reach out first. It's a system, not a one-off campaign, and it's backed by a simple guarantee: 30 qualified conversations in 90 days.</p>

  <h2>Who we serve</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sourcing agencies</strong> winning Western Amazon sellers.</li>
    <li><strong>Freight forwarders</strong> winning importers and e-commerce brands.</li>
    <li><strong>Software / SaaS</strong> filling their demo calendar with supply-chain and e-commerce buyers.</li>
    <li><strong>Factories</strong> winning direct buyers instead of losing margin to middlemen.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who’s behind it</h2>
  <p>China Wins Global is led by <strong>Tehsin</strong>, who built the system after seeing how much world-class Chinese supply loses to a simple absence of trust online. We run a boutique operation — a small number of clients at a time, so every account gets senior attention.</p>

